<h3 style="color: #b23233; text-align: center;"><strong>*</strong></h3>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Third place (3-way tie, 5 mentions):<br />
</strong></h5>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247576" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/lucas-schaefer-the-slip/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Lucas-Schaefer-The-Slip-.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Lucas Schaefer, The Slip" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Lucas Schaefer, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668030707&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Slip&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Jack Smyth (Simon &amp;amp; Schuster, June)&lt;/p&gt;
